NATO apologizes for Afghan civilian deaths      (AP)
AP - A NATO airstrike targeting insurgents fighting from a residential compound in the volatile southwestern province of Helmand inadvertently killed at least nine civilians, NATO officials said on Monday, although the actual tally of civilian deaths remains unclear due to varying official accounts.
AP Exclusive: Syria to end nuclear secrecy      (AP)
AP - In a major turnaround, Syria is pledging full cooperation with U.N. attempts to probe strong evidence that it secretly built a reactor that could have been used to make nuclear arms, according to a confidential document shared with The Associated Press on Sunday.

